.START 

Canadian manufacturers registered a 1.6% increase in unfilled orders in July, Statistics Canada, a government agency, said. 

The order backlog at July 31 totaled 30.76 billion Canadian dollars (US$26 billion), up from C$30.28 billion in June.
The July increase followed three consecutive monthly decreases. 

Manufacturers' shipments rose 0.1% from June and inventories rose 0.6%.
The inventories to shipments ratio rose to 1.56-to-1 in July from 1.55-to-1 in June. 

